snippet.title: Update: Police issue Amber Alert for 5-year-old allegedly abducted by 3 men
snippet.description:
Update: Police issue Amber Alert for 5-year-old allegedly abducted by 3 men




Police have delivered an Amber Alert after a 5-year-old girl was reportedly  by three men in Texas, bestowing to reports.
ABC News say the vigilant for Maleah Davis of Houston was issued on May 5. The girl was last seen wearing a blue zip-up jacket, blue jeans, running shoe, and a pink curtsy in her hair.
Maleah’s stepfather, 26-year-old Darion Vence, says that three men beaten him before taking the girl and leaving he and his 2-year-old son behind.
Reports claim that Maleah was last seen at around 9 p.m. on Saturday night, at the same time as the three unidentified males are thought to be driving a 2010 blue Chevrolet truck. The license number for the vehicle has not been revealed, but the accused were spotted last on the Southwest Freeway near State Highway 6 in Sugar Land, around 20 miles south of Houston.



Houston Police
Twitted..
Better quality, color photo taken by traffic camera of the stolen Nissan Altima with tags 330-92G9.
Stepfather Darion Venceutters that the three men worn  him up during a car theft and briefly held him and his son detainee. As per reports, he later told police that he and the toddler were neglected on the side of the road, but Maleah was taken.
Sgt. Mark Holbrook of the Houston Police Department set that Vence said he was in and out of mindfulness during the incident. At one point he woke up to find the suspects driving him and the two children around in a blue pickup 

Houston Police
Twitted.

1/2: Photos showed at the media briefing: first is target's stolen car, a silver 2011 Nissan Altima with TX paper tags 3092G9, seen on a traffic camera near Hwy 59 & State Hwy 6 in Sugar Land about 3 pm Saturday (May 4). Second is photo similarity of suspects' blue truck.
We’d love the public to help us so we can write out the blanks in this story. I understand there are a lot of blanks in that story, but we’re hoping the public can fill in the blanks,” Holbrook told reporters on Sunday late afternoon.
Vence told police that he and the kids were on their way to pick up his mate on Friday night at George Bush International Airport. He noticed something wrong with the car and drew over.
“He hears a cracking noise like he has a flat tire, pulls over to check on it,” Holbrook said.
“Agreeing to Darion, what occurs next is a blue pickup truck pulls up behind him, two Hispanic men get out. One of them makes a statement, saying that Maleah looks very nice, looks very sweet. The other male knockouts Darion in the head. Darion loses cognizance.”

Houston Police
Twitted.

Anyone with statistics on Maleah's locations is advised to contact HPD Homicide at 713-308-3600 or @CrimeStopHOU at 713-222-TIPS. Media partners: all updates on this case will be disseminated here
Anyone with any info is urged to communicate HPD Homicide at 713-308-3600 or @CrimeStopHOU at 713-222-TIPS. We’re praying for Maleah’s safe coming back!

Please share this story so we can get the word out there!
